&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;THIS IS AN INTERNAL VACANCY AND ONLY CURRENT EMPLOYEES OF BERKSHIRE HEALTHCARE SHOULD APPLY&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Assistant Practitioner, Wokingham Community Nursing Service&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Finchampstead TEAM&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;37.5hours Fixed-Term until 31st October 2022&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently recruiting for a Band 4 Assistant Practitioner to join one of our busy dynamic Community Nursing teams within the Wokingham locality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role of Assistant Practitioner is fundamental to the success of Community Nursing Teams. The post holder will be able to demonstrate the competencies required to perform at this level and role model the Trust’s core values well as exhibit the behaviours required as part of those values. Our nurses work Mon to Fri, 8.30am to 16.30pm (with approximately one weekend a month and bank holidays in rotation). You may also be required to cover the 4.30-7pm Teatime shift on a Rota basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It is essential that you have the Assistant Practitioner Qualification and with a good understanding of the modern NHS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting colleagues in the delivery of compassionate, safe and structured care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and provide treatment in collaboration with others as appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To thrive in community nursing, you also need the people skills to work effectively with colleagues and patients of all kinds - you must listen well and communicate concisely.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It&#39;s important that you have a calm approach and the ability to priorities and work in a busy team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A driving license and access to a car is essential, due to the travel involved&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Some of the benefits of joining our team:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AfC Salary ranging from £22,987 - £25,365 per annum (incl of HCAS&lt;em&gt;)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working opportunities and a strong emphasis on your work, life balance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual leave – 27 days for new starters, plus bank holidays. Increasing to 29 days after 5 years and 33 days after 10 years NHS service. Pro rata for part time staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent learning and development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary sacrifice scheme for a new car&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous maternity, paternity and adoption leave for eligible staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced IT enablement and support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidential telephone care service providing independent support and advice for staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;And so much more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The 4 “must haves” for you to be considered for this role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Previous Experience as an Assistant Practitioner Community Nursing&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Have the ability to work without direct supervision, at times delivering care independently in line with the individual’s defined plan of care, within the parameters of practice of the Assistant Practitioner role, accessing clinical and care advice when needed&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervise and delegate appropriately to support staff within the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Car driver with ability and readiness to travel to multiple sites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you recognise yourself in these requirements, we would recommend you apply today!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are happy to answer any questions that you may have. Please don’t hesitate to call: Saiyad Allymamod on 07930914721 or email: saiyad.allymamod@berkshire.nhs.uk who’ll be delighted to help.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSaiyad AllymamodJob titleTeam ManagerEmail addresssaiyad.allymamod@berkshire.nhs.ukTelephone number07930914721&lt;/p&gt;
